(3) The Board may, with the consent of the Minister, by statutory instrument, make rules— (a) providing for the administration of any National Museum ; (b) providing for the preservation of objects required for the purposes of National Museums; (c) providing for the charging of fees for admission to any National Museum by members of the public; and (d) prescribing the articles which shall not be introduced into a National Museum without the consent of the officer in charge of that National Museum .
